## Limitations
The report is limited by the availability of up-to-date and comprehensive data on the consequences of not registering to vote. Additionally, the perspectives gathered from platforms like Quora may not fully represent the broader public opinion or the nuanced implications of voter registration laws. The report also does not cover international contexts extensively, focusing primarily on the United States.

